uthor/aryansurendranath-xda/\"\u003eMakeUseOf\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n                        \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e While traveling through Japan, my phone was running on overtime. It was my go-to for navigation, translation, photos; you name it, and my phone did it. Having it at 100% power required some active thinking on my part. But, a power bank, which I could easily carry to the hotel breakfast or a convenience store, made this easier.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eIn this case, I defaulted to the \u003ca href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Anker-Magnetic-Upgraded-Foldable-Interstellar/dp/B0B466YTT3/?tag=makeusw-20\u0026amp;ascsubtag=UUmuoUeUpU2035262\u0026amp;asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.makeuseof.com%2Fbest-power-banks-for-traveling-abroad%2F\u0026amp;asc_campaign=Evergreen\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow\"\u003eAnker MagGo 5,000mAh power bank\u003c/a\u003e. I\u0026#39;ve had it since September 2023, and it\u0026#39;s held up well. It can even fully charge my phone.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eWith its 5,000mAh capacity, I get a full charge whenever I use it to charge my iPhone wirelessly. If wired charging, this increases to a full charge and then some. But since it supports MagSafe—making it one of the \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/best-magsafe-accessories/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ebest magnetic accessories for the iPhone\u003c/a\u003e—I didn\u0026#39;t always pack an extra cable.\u003c/p\u003e    \n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/01/anker-magsafe-power-bank-in-stand-mode-on-a-tabl